import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Methodology" currentPath="/methodology/">
  <h1>Methodology</h1>
  <p class="lead">
    How Caesar AI Regulation Watch curates pilot data. This site is a <strong>public pilot</strong> and{" "}
    <strong>technical MVP candidate</strong> — official-source-first, human-review gated, not legal advice,
    not complete coverage, and not client evidence.
  </p>

  <div class="prose">
    <h2>Official-source-first</h2>
    <p>
      Primary truth for every law, guidance, and change record is the <strong>registered official URL</strong>
      on the relevant authority or legislature site. This preview summarises metadata to support governance
      review — it does not replace reading official sources.
    </p>

    <h2>Source credibility</h2>
    <p>Each source in the registry carries a credibility tier:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Official primary</strong> — primary legal or regulator publication (e.g. EUR-Lex, Datatilsynet).</li>
      <li><strong>Official secondary</strong> — another official body publication linked to the topic.</li>
      <li><strong>Authoritative reference</strong> — used sparingly; always secondary to official sources.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Manual sample records (v0.4.x)</h2>
    <p>
      Law, guidance, and change entries in the pilot are <strong>manual samples</strong> with{" "}
      <code>record_origin: manual_sample</code>. They validate the data model and site — they are{" "}
      <strong>not</strong> automated watcher output. Sample dates and summaries may be fictionalised for
      schema testing.
    </p>

    <h2>Review status workflow</h2>
    <p>Curated content uses a review lifecycle:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>draft</strong> / <strong>pending_review</strong> — not approved for client use.</li>
      <li><strong>reviewed</strong> — Control Tower has approved URLs and scope for publication.</li>
      <li><strong>needs_update</strong> — source or record may be stale.</li>
      <li><strong>rejected_for_client_use</strong> — do not use in deliverables.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      <strong>Human review is required</strong> before using any record in client work, consulting memos, or
      compliance claims — even when marked reviewed.
    </p>

    <h2>Watcher prototype (manual only)</h2>
    <p>
      A <strong>manual CLI watcher prototype</strong> (page metadata, RSS, and narrow API adapters) exists for
      pilot sources. Outputs are <code>pending_review</code> detected changes — not automatic record updates.
      Watchers respect rate limits and hub policy; they are <strong>not</strong> run on a production schedule and
      are <strong>not</strong> in CI. The public change feed still includes manual samples; simulated detected
      changes are clearly marked.
    </p>
    <p>
      Cautious <strong>live metadata checks</strong> (allowlisted official URLs, metadata only) and a{" "}
      <strong>manual GitHub Actions artifact workflow</strong> support human triage. Metadata deltas are{" "}
      <strong>not</strong> legal or regulatory change claims.
    </p>

    <h2>Global coverage map (v0.5.1)</h2>
    <p>
      The <a href="/map/">coverage map</a> uses a <strong>static SVG projection</strong> from manually curated
      latitude/longitude fields in jurisdiction YAML. Markers are <strong>display aids only</strong> — they do
      not represent legal territorial boundaries, sovereignty claims, or complete geographic coverage. No remote
      map tiles are loaded.
    </p>

    <h2>Human review queue (v0.5.1)</h2>
    <p>
      The <a href="/review-queue/">review queue</a> lists items with <code>review_status</code> other than{" "}
      <code>reviewed</code>, plus timeline events not verified on source. It is <strong>read-only</strong> — it
      does not update YAML, mark items reviewed, or replace qualified legal review.
    </p>

    <h2>Coverage limits</h2>
    <p>
      The registry covers a <strong>curated subset</strong> of global official sources starting from EU/Norway.
      We do <strong>not</strong> claim complete global legal coverage, exhaustive instrument lists, or
      up-to-date status without verification on official sites.
    </p>

    <h2>Control and evidence mapping</h2>
    <p>
      Export samples link regulatory changes to draft <code>regulation_watch.control.*</code> and{" "}
      <code>regulation_watch.evidence.*</code> references. These are alignment drafts pending{" "}
      <code>caesar-ai-evidence</code> — they do not create client evidence automatically.
    </p>
  </div>

  <p><a href="/disclaimer/">Read full disclaimer →</a></p>
</BaseLayout>
